dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-yh8r,related,"2026-07-12T19:14:50.801Z",null,null
body: "## Why (2026-07-12 maintainer directive: too many files per folder + too-long files; document-only pass)\nThe intra-file effective-LOC half of this directive class is owned by pm-yh8r (census current as of its 2026-07-12 note; sdk/runtime.ts 3388/3400 is #1 at-risk). THIS item owns the inter-file half: tracked-file fan-out per source directory. Census (git ls-files, direct children only):\n\n- src/cli/commands 72 (~55 command modules interleaved with ~17 cross-command helper modules; `extension/` and `test/` subfolders already exist as grouping precedent)\n- tests/unit/commands 60 (mirror of the above)\n- tests/integration 32 · scripts 23 · tests/unit/scripts 23 · src/cli 19 · src/core/shared 18 · docs 18 · src/sdk 16 · src/core/item 16 · src/core/extensions 16 · tests/helpers 16\n\nOUT OF SCOPE: `.agents/pm/**` fan-out (history 1758, tasks 567, issues 397) — tracker-store bucketing is owned by pm-0qg5 (format_version-gated migration); never double-file.\n\n## Target policy\n- Soft ceiling ~20 direct files per source directory; exceedances need a grouping move or a documented exemption in this body.\n- Group by DOMAIN NOUN (align with the pm-n7rr grammar nouns), never by file kind — no `utils/`/`helpers/` dumping grounds; a single `shared/` module folder per level is the one sanctioned exception.\n- Tests mirror src 1:1 — every src move carries its mirrored spec move in the same commit.\n\n## Disposition blueprint (per directory)\n1. src/cli/commands (72 → ≤20 root + noun subfolders):\n   - Cross-command support → `commands/shared/`: event-validation-messages, item-filter-options, legacy-none-tokens, lifecycle-transitions, linked-artifacts, linked-test-entry, linked-test-parsers, list-filter-shared, metadata-normalizers, mutation-command-options, recurrence-parsers, repeatable-metadata-parsers, scheduling-shortcuts, search-pagination, search-rendering, shared-unset-fields, init-agent-guidance.\n   - Noun families into per-noun folders (extension/ + test/ precedent): `history/` (history, history-compact, history-redact, history-repair) · `test/` (test, test-all, test-runs joining existing linked-command-detection) · `annotations/` (notes, learnings, comments, comments-audit) · `maintenance/` (normalize, reindex, gc, dedupe-audit, dedupe-merge).\n   - Remaining single-verb modules stay at root.\n2. src/cli (19 direct): help family (help-content, help-json-payload, guide-topics, commander-usage, error-guidance) → `cli/help/`; parser family (shared-parsers, argv-utils, bootstrap-args) → `cli/parsing/`; register-* + registration-helpers stay (registration IS this folder's identity); main.ts stays (entry point, wired in package/bin).\n3. scripts (23 direct): smoke-*.mjs + plugin-mcp-smoke-harness.mjs → `scripts/smoke/`; release-version.mjs, generate-release-notes.mjs, sync-versions.mjs → `scripts/release/`; bundle-cli.mjs, prepare-build-cache.mjs, finalize-build.mjs, gen-*.mjs → `scripts/build/`; run-tests.mjs + install.sh/install.ps1 + check-secrets*.mjs STAY at root (README curl paths, CI invocations, contributor muscle memory) — verify EVERY consumer (package.json scripts, .github/workflows, docs, other scripts) before moving any script.\n4. tests/integration (32): group by surface — `cli/`, `mcp/`, `extensions/`, `release/`, `telemetry/`; tests/unit/scripts follows the scripts/ regrouping mirror.\n5. AT-threshold, no move yet (re-evaluate at T6): src/core/shared 18 (it is the sanctioned shared level), src/sdk 16 (PR#396 barrel split + cli-contracts/ already relieved it; pm-usfg partition will re-shape it), src/core/item 16, src/core/extensions 16, tests/helpers 16.\n6. docs 18: navigated via the AGENTS.md progressive-disclosure map, not by folder browsing — exempt.\n\n## Constraints (why this is not a mechanical mv)\n- Zero feature/behavior loss: bin entry, package exports, contract tables, MCP tool surface, completion output byte-identical; moves are import-specifier-only refactors.\n- Sequencing fence: files inside the SDK-promotion partition (pm-usfg slices pm-3mna/pm-zwpp/pm-oxrw/pm-4a7m/pm-oslr) and pm-yh8r decomposition targets move WITH their slice/split, never in a separate churn pass — one migration per file, no double conflict surface against active lanes.\n- Reference-churn checklist per tranche: ESM relative import specifiers (.js), vitest.config.ts path-keyed excludes (big legacy files listed by path), eslint-suppressions.json path keys (A+ source of truth, max 17), coverage literal all-src globs, package.json script paths, .github/workflows script invocations, docs command examples, jscpd/CodeFactor path baselines.\n- pm tracked file-links: every moved path strands `pm files` links → files_missing rises above the 155/122 baseline owned by pm-j8z6. Each tranche updates links on OPEN items it touches; closed-item drift is handed to the pm-j8z6 reconciliation (CREATE-ONLY on closed items — never mutate them).\n- `git mv` per file for rename detection; ONE directory family per PR tranche, each independently green through the full gate set.\n\n## Tranche order (each tranche = one PR)\nT1 scripts/ regrouping (lowest blast radius, zero src imports) → T2 tests/integration surface folders → T3 src/cli/commands `shared/` extraction → T4 src/cli/commands noun folders (excluding usfg/yh8r-fenced files) → T5 src/cli help/ + parsing/ → T6 re-census + threshold re-check after the pm-usfg partition lands."
